he scala tympani. 13. In the absence of deliberate sound stimulation, the hair cell voltage fluctuated continuously a out its mean level. The principal frequency components in the noise were concentrated around the c.f. of the cell. The voltage noise in the hair cells showed no significant cross-correlation with sound pressure fluctuations at the tympanum.},
